SIMPLE: success
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Success
<hw>Suc*cess"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>successus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>succ⟦egrave⟧s</ets>. See
<er>Succeed</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Act of succeeding;
succession.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then all the sons of these five brethren reigned⟦br⟧
By due <qex>success</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which comes after; hence, consequence, issue,
or result, of an endeavor or undertaking, whether good or bad; the
outcome of effort.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Men . . . that are like to do that, that is committed to them, and
to report back again faithfully the <qex>success</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Perplexed and troubled at his bad <qex>success</qex>⟦br⟧
The tempter stood.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The favorable or prosperous termination of anything
attempted; the attainment of a proposed object; prosperous
issue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Dream of <qex>success</qex> and happy victory!</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Or teach with more <qex>success</qex> her son⟦br⟧
The vices of the time to shun.</q> <rj><qau>Waller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Military <qex>successes</qex>, above all others, elevate the minds
of a people.</q> <rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>That which meets with, or one who accomplishes,
favorable results, as a play or a player.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1439 --></p>

<p><ent>Successary</ent>⟦br⟧
